Bring a #medium pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Trim
@scallions{2}. Cut scallion whites crosswise into 1-inch pieces; thinly slice
greens. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, half the
@sesame seeds{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), @sugar{1/2%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp},
and as many @?korean chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. Set aside to pickle.

Once water is boiling, add @ramen noodles{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Drain and thoroughly rinse under cold water until cooled, about ~{30%seconds}.
Toss with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}; set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pot used for noodles over medium-high heat. Add
@bok choy and napa cabbage{4%oz}, @shredded carrots{4%oz}, and scallion whites;
season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a pinch of @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until browned and tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Reduce heat to medium.

Thoroughly shake @coconut milk{1} in container before opening.

Add @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, @peanut butter{1.15%oz}, and half
the coconut milk (you'll use more in the next step) to pot with veggies; stir to
combine. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium low. Cook until sauce is
slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add drained noodles to pot; toss to combine. If needed, stir in remaining
coconut milk a splash at a time until everything is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Remove pot from heat; stir in half the cucumber pickling liquid. Taste and
season with salt and pepper if needed.

Divide stir-fry between #bowls{} and arrange pickled cucumber (draining first)
alongside. Top with scallion greens, cilantro, remaining sesame seeds, and as
many remaining chili flakes as you like. Serve.